Package Tanks

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    App
    The main application class for the tank game, managing game initialization, input handling, game state updates, and rendering.
    Bomb
    Represents a bomb in the game, managing its physics, display, and interactions with the terrain and tanks.
    HUD
    Handles the display of various heads-up display (HUD) elements in the Tanks game, such as health bars, fuel icons, parachutes, and game-ending messages.
    Parachute
    Represents a parachute for a tank, managing deployment and effects on the tank during falls.
    Powerups
    Manages power-ups for tanks, including repairs, fuel refills, and additional parachutes.
    Tank
    Represents a tank in the game, managing its position, health, fuel, power level, and interactions with terrain and other game elements.
    Terrain
    Represents the terrain in the tank game, including the graphical representation, terrain obstacles, and specific locations for trees and tanks.
    Wind
    Represents the wind in the game, managing its speed and the display of wind indicators.
